      • getTestPaths

        public static java.util.List<coverage.graph.Path> getTestPaths​(java.lang.String edges,
                                                               java.lang.String initialNodes,
                                                               java.lang.String finalNodes,
                                                               TestCoverageCriteria criterion)
                                                        throws coverage.web.InvalidInputException,
                                                               coverage.graph.InvalidGraphException
        Generates test paths to satisfy the edge coverage criterion.
        Parameters:
        edges - edges of a control flow graph in a String format "1 2 \n 2 3 \n"
        initialNodes - initial nodes of a control flow graph in a String format "1 2 ... etc."
        finalNodes - final nodes of a control flow graph in a String format "1 2 ... etc."
        criterion - an enumeration type of TestCoverageCriteria
        Returns:
        a list of Path objects that satisfy edge coverage
        Throws:
        coverage.web.InvalidInputException - when any of edges, initialNodes, and finalNodes is in a wrong format
        coverage.graph.InvalidGraphException - when the graph cannot be correctly constructed from the specified inputs
